   <annotation>
      <appInfo>
         <meta.section type="examples"/>
      </appInfo>
      <documentation>
         The following is an example of the &lt;code&gt;targetLocations&lt;/code&gt; extension:
&lt;pre&gt;
	&lt;extension
		id=&quot;org.eclipse.pde.core.customlocation&quot;
		name=&quot;Custom Location&quot;
		point=&quot;org.eclipse.pde.core.targetLocations&quot;&gt;
		&lt;targetLocation
			locationFactory=&quot;org.eclipse.pde.core.CustomLocationFactory&quot;
			type=&quot;CustomLocation&quot;&gt;
		&lt;/targetLocation&gt;
	&lt;/extension&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;

In the example above, the name and id of the target are declared in the plugin.xml, but the factory &lt;code&gt;org.eclipse.pde.core.CustomLocationFactory&lt;/code&gt; to create the target location comes from the contributing plug-in.
      </documentation>
   </annotation>

   <annotation>
      <appInfo>
         <meta.section type="apiinfo"/>
      </appInfo>
      <documentation>
         A Target Location will provide a factory that shall provide the initialized target location object. The target location can be added to PDE UI wizards by supplying following Adaptor factories (using adapters extension).

String to IWizardNode: This shall take the target location identifier (String) and return the appropriate IWizardNode object to supply the wizard to create a new location.
String to ILabelWizard: This shall take the target location identifier (String) and return a label provider that will supply the text and image for the target location (to be used for displaying)
      </documentation>
   </annotation>


